perl, though that uses lists rather than multiple value or fixed-size tuples:<p><pre><code>  #!&#x2F;usr&#x2F;bin&#x2F;env perl
  use v5.36;

  sub f($a, $b) {
    return ($a+1, $b+1);
  }

  sub g($k, $l) {
    return ($k+1, $l+1);
  }

  say for f(g(1,2));
</code></pre>
prints out<p><pre><code>  3
  4</code></pre>

